column5: Got out with Wink for a few hours on Sunday.  Here he is with a couple. Nothing huge, but lots of em!      will be back at it this weekend.
What an interesting set up he has! Must be challenging landing those bass from the kayak!
Sweet console, is that the 140 - doesn't seem as long as I had thought if it is.  Nice fish too
Nice report Teamster!  Dang, Stoty sure set the bar high for a 21 1/2 inch bass.  Nice looking fishies.
nice fish!  i got to stop and through a few casts next time im that way, i keep hearing the smallies are awesome out there  cheers!
It's a Pungo 120. Stick with SOT's or you'll wish after that you had...  just my opinion.  Wink(guy in pics) is going for a sit-on top now.  Biggest thing is to look at them all before you decide.

21-1/2" is impressive for sure!  We'll be fishing near the mouth soon and then I'll start measuring.  They get real big moving in/out lake to river and there's nice largies there too.  I never remember the OFC sign.
